properties.areaDesc: East Slopes of the Washington Cascades
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 22 at 5:38AM PST until January 22 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Pendleton OR
properties.description:
...SNOW TODAY...

.A front will bring snow to the Washington Cascades and the
Northern Blue Mountains today. Snow levels will begin to rise
later today eventually changing precipitation to rain below 5000
feet.

* WHAT...Moderate snow expected below 3000 feet. Total snow
accumulations of up to 5 inches below 3000 feet around Cle
Elum and Easton. Higher amounts are expected near the Cascade
crest with 8 to 12 inches possible above 3000 feet.

* WHERE...East Slopes of the central Washington Cascades...
mainly in western Kittitas County.

* WHEN...From 7 AM to 10 PM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Precipitation will begin to change over to
rain this evening as snow levels rise.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PST THIS EVENING BELOW 3000 FEET
